The security guard of his office building said, "About one-third of them either didn't come or the company announced bankruptcy," and the rent of office buildings has also dropped across the board. The man also said that in addition to office buildings, many shops along the street are now closed, and they are in the downtown area.
The media "One Real Estate" recently reported: The rent of the core area Nanjing West Road section has fallen below 10 yuan. According to Colliers International data, in the fourth quarter of last year, the vacancy rate of Grade A office buildings in Shanghai was about to break the international 20% warning line, and the rent fell month-on-month to 6.54 yuan per square meter per day.
In addition to the South Bund, where the vacancy rate is over 10%, the vacancy rate of the Xintiandi section is as high as 21%. Among the 18 secondary core areas, 13 sections have a vacancy rate of more than 20%

content: Reuters quoted a White House official as saying that US President Trump signed a memorandum on Friday instructing the US Foreign Investment Committee to restrict Chinese investment in strategic areas. The official told Reuters that the memorandum specifically targets China's "increasing use of US capital to develop and modernize its military, intelligence and other security agencies" and requires CFIUS to restrict Chinese investment in key US sectors such as technology, critical infrastructure, healthcare and energy. The official also said that the Trump administration will consider imposing new or expanded restrictions on US outbound investment in China in sensitive technology fields, including semiconductors, AI artificial intelligence, quantum, biotechnology, and aerospace.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
The Chinese government spends less on its citizens than most countries with similar or higher income levels, a Financial Times analysis shows, which could undermine Beijing's efforts to encourage consumption to boost its sluggish economy.
The Chinese government spends only about 6% of GDP on personal consumption (including services that directly benefit citizens, such as health care and social security), while household spending accounts for 38% of GDP, according to the World Bank.
China is classified as an upper-middle-income country by the World Bank, but its government personal consumption expenditure lags behind most of the BRICS countries, according to data analysis
"Without deeper social welfare reforms, people will save all these precautionary savings instead of spending them," said the criminal law expert.
Economists expect Beijing to increase its planned central government budget deficit from 3% of GDP to 4% next month and announce more government bonds to help boost the economy...
fullContent:
《金融时报》的分析显示，中国政府在公民身上的支出低于大多数收入水平相近或更高的国家，这可能会破坏北京方面鼓励消费以提振疲软经济的努力。
 世界银行的数据显示，中国政府仅将GDP的6%左右用于个人消费（包括医疗保健、社会保障等直接惠及公民的服务），而家庭支出则占GDP的38%。
 数据分析显示，中国被世界银行列为中上等收入国家，但其政府个人消费支出落后于金砖国家中的大多数成员国
刑法学家说：“如果不进行更深入的社会福利改革，人们将会把这些预防性储蓄全部存起来，而不是去消费。”
 经济学家预计，北京方面下个月将把计划中的中央政府预算赤字从占GDP的3％提高到4％，并宣布发行更多政府债券以帮助推动经济增长

content:
Media person Xiang Dongliang: Recently, many platforms have successively issued announcements that they will gradually pay social security for food delivery riders. However, Meituan is expected to have 820,000 full-time and stable riders. If the five insurances and one housing fund are paid according to the minimum base, 15.5 billion yuan will be spent each year, while Meituan's net profit in 2023 is more than 13.8 billion yuan. Therefore, it is impossible for the platform to fully bear the social security costs of the riders. The platform will only take the lead in opening social security accounts for the riders and deduct funds on their behalf every month.
JD's so-called promise to buy insurance for riders refers to the purchase of social security for the new full-time food delivery riders, and the scale of this group of riders is expected to be around 10,000, accounting for less than 1% of all JD riders, and even less than a fraction of the number of riders that Meituan promised to buy social security.
